Includes note dated 1989 December: "This album shows some of the rehabilitation work performed on the Berkshire Line, most of which had been out of service/abandoned 
for 17 years until reopening in April 1989. The Housatonic Railroad has performed all rehabilitation work with its own employees and equipment under a joint FRA / Connecticut DOT / Housatonic project.
One each page the top photo was taken in September 1988 and the bottom picture in November 1989 at the following locations: 1 - Boardman's Bridge, New Milford; 2 - Gaylordsville; 
3 - South Kent Road, South Kent; 4 - Bulls Bridge Road, South Kent; 5 - Camp Getaway, Kent; 6 - Route 7, Kent; 7 - Just north of Route 7 Crossing, Kent; 8 - Kent Falls; 9 - Just north of Kent Falls;
10 - Cornwall Bridge (No Sept. 1988 photo); 11 - Route 128, West Cornwall (No Sept. 1988 photo); 12 - Route 126 & Sand Road Crossings, Falls Village."
